{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is cross-module wiring (collector/adapter outputs handed to the summary input). A single-function unit test is too narrow because the risk is missing or dropped source data at handoff. Real OS/network/subprocess behavior is not required for this behavior; stubbed source clients are sufficient. Higher levels were considered and rejected: System is disqualified because behavior text only requires inclusion of three source payloads, not real network failure semantics; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no real model-output correctness or multi-agent sequence is stated.","test_description":"Wire the real aggregation/orchestration modules with three in-process fake source adapters that return distinct sentinel payloads. Execute one report build and assert the exact object/text sent to summary-generation contains all three source sections with correct source attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is about fault-tolerant orchestration across modules: one adapter fails, pipeline continues, placeholder propagates into report sections. That is a module-boundary/state-propagation failure mode, so Unit is too low. Real infrastructure is not strictly required because an in-process adapter raising the same failure class can trigger the path. Higher levels were considered and rejected: System is disqualified since behavior text does not require validating real timeout/socket/HTTP behavior, only fallback handling; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no model judgment is part of correctness.","test_description":"Use real report pipeline modules with three adapters, forcing one adapter to fail (exception/failed result contract) while two return valid data. Assert run completion, no abort, and the output report includes a `data unavailable` marker only for the failed section.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"As written, the behavior targets transformation fidelity from provided input data to summary content, which can be validated at the summary component boundary without I/O. No explicit requirement references real network, subprocesses, or a real AI model. Higher levels were considered and rejected: Integration is disqualified because behavior text does not require cross-module handoff, only correctness of summary output given input; Agentic is disqualified because the behavior does not explicitly state LLM/ML-dependent quality or non-deterministic model decisions.","test_description":"Call the summary-generation function/component directly with a fixed structured input fixture containing key metrics/issues/deploy counts, then assert the generated narrative preserves those key values (including signs/trends/units) and does not contradict them.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"If implementation actually uses a real LLM call for this step, this should be upgraded to Agentic.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.56,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to an inbox, which crosses process/network/external email infrastructure boundaries. In-process fakes can pass while real SMTP/API auth, routing, MIME, or delivery semantics fail. Therefore System is the minimum to catch real failure. Higher levels were considered and rejected: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because the asserted outcome is transport/delivery correctness, not model decision quality across agentic stages.","test_description":"Run the scheduled/report job end-to-end against reachable test instances/services and a real test mailbox. Verify data collection, report assembly, send operation success, and message arrival in the configured inbox with expected subject/body structure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure mode includes real service unreachability plus persistence across runs; mocks often hide true connectivity/error-shape behavior and retry-trigger conditions seen with real email transport failures. Local file persistence can be integration-tested, but the unreachable-service boundary is real infrastructure, so System is the safer minimum. Higher levels were considered and rejected: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because behavior is deterministic transport fallback/retry logic with no model-output dependence.","test_description":"Execute run 1 with email endpoint intentionally unreachable in a system-like environment; assert report persisted to disk in retry queue/state. Execute run 2 with service restored; assert queued report is retried and delivered, and local queued artifact/state is cleared or marked sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
